@CraftyCampusCarl
Just finished my final project for Sculpture 101 – a lamp made entirely from recycled textbooks! The base is a stack of old econ books, and the shade is pages woven together. It was a ton of work, but so worth it. The hardest part was wiring the light safely – shoutout to my engineering roommate for the help!

It's sitting on my desk now and gives off this amazing warm, scholarly glow. Perfect for late-night study sessions. I'm thinking of making more as gifts for graduation. What do you all think – should I start an Etsy shop? #DIY #Upcycle #CampusLife #StudentArt
